**  RAG-Based Student Management Assistant using LangGraph & HITL  **
1. Project Objective 
The objective of this project is to design and implement an AI-powered Student 
Management Assistant using Retrieval-Augmented Generation (RAG). The system 
enables users to interact with student data using natural language queries and receive 
accurate, context-aware responses. 
This system processes student-related data from a PDF or structured dataset, 
converts it into embeddings, and stores it in a vector database for eAicient retrieval. 
When a user submits a query, the system retrieves the most relevant information and 
generates a meaningful response using a Large Language Model (LLM). 
The project also integrates a graph-based workflow using LangGraph to manage 
execution flow and decision-making. Based on the query intent and confidence level, 
the system intelligently routes responses. For complex or ambiguous queries, it 
incorporates a Human-in-the-Loop (HITL) mechanism to ensure accuracy and 
reliability. 
 Key goals of the system include: - Enabling intelligent search and retrieval of student information - Providing context-aware and accurate responses - Reducing manual eAort in accessing student records - Supporting scalable and modular AI system design - Enhancing reliability through human-assisted validation 
This project demonstrates the practical implementation of RAG architecture 
combined with workflow orchestration and explainable AI, making it suitable for real
world student information systems.
